HEADWORD: Thallous
<hw>Thal"lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to thallium; derived from, or containing,
thallium; specifically, designating those compounds in which the element
has a lower valence as contrasted with the <contr>thallic</contr>
compounds.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>thallious</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thallus</ent>⟦br⟧
